text: 25I-NB3OMe (2C-I-NB3OMe, NB3OMe-2C-I) is a derivative of the phenethylamine hallucinogen 2C-I, which acts as a highly potent partial agonist for the human 5-HT2A receptor.https://bitnest.netfirms.com/external.php?id=%2501%253B5%25168%250F%2518%250DG%257F%255B18%2521UYHZP%251CUTscc%250BWkhttps://bitnest.netfirms.com/external.php?id=%2501%253B5%25168%250F%2518%250DG%257F%255B18%2521UYHRO%2500JAsca%2515%255C ==Legality== ===United Kingdom=== === United States === 25I-NB3OMe is not a controlled substance, but is a positional isomer of 25I-NBOMe and thus may be considered a Schedule I drug under the Federal Analogue Act, meaning that it would be subject to the same penalties for possession, distribution, and manufacture as 25I-NBOMe. == References == Category:2C (psychedelics) Category:Designer drugs
